      "Microstructure_Info": {
        "Microstructure_Text": {
          "original": "FCC+L12 dual-phase structure. Average grain size 9.2 μm, significantly reduced from 29.7 μm due to discontinuous precipitation (DP). Average KAM value 0.67°, reduced indicating partial dislocation annihilation. Two distinct regions observed: Continuous Precipitation (CP) region with cellular structures and Discontinuous Precipitation (DP) region with stripe-shaped contrast and lamellar L12 nanorods. L12 phase identified by {001} and {011} superlattice spots in SADP. STEM-EDS and APT confirm L12 nanorods enriched in Ni, Al, Ti and depleted in Co, Cr. Cellular boundaries in DP region show L12-like segregation (Ti, Ni, Al enrichment; Co, Cr depletion). Volume fraction of L12 ~37% calculated by lever rule. Highly coherent interface between L12 and FCC matrix (δ=0.28%).",
          "simplified": "FCC+L12 dual-phase with grain refinement to 9.2 μm; lamellar L12 nanorods enriched in Ni/Al/Ti, depleted in Co/Cr; ~37 vol% L12; coherent interface δ=0.28%; DP regions with stripe contrast vs CP regions with cellular structures"
        },
